        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 12:21AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1221 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles west of Terrell County Gas Plant, or 22 miles north of Dryden,
moving north at 70 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sheffield, Iraan Municipal Airport, Terrell County Gas Plant, and
Iraan.

This includes Interstate 10 between mile markers 305 and 327.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
